# Frontend Conventions

## Styling — Emotion only, no Tailwind

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — Tailwind
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-4">

// ✅ GOOD — Emotion via component.styled.ts
<Container>
  <Content>
```

## Folder-based components with `component.styled.ts`

```
components/
  PoolCard/
    PoolCard.tsx              ← JSX only, imports from .styled.ts
    PoolCard.styled.ts        ← all Emotion styles
    PoolCard.types.ts         ← interfaces/types (if non-trivial)
    index.ts                  ← re-export
```

```ts
// PoolCard.styled.ts
import styled from '@emotion/styled';

export const Root = styled.div`
  background: #1a1a2e;
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 16px;
`;

export const Title = styled.h3`
  font-size: 14px;
  color: #a0a0b0;
`;
```

```tsx
// PoolCard.tsx
import { Root, Title } from './PoolCard.styled';
import type { PoolCardProps } from './PoolCard.types';

export function PoolCard({ pool, playerCount }: PoolCardProps) {
  return (
    <Root>
      <Title>{pool} site</Title>
    </Root>
  );
}
```

## Keep business logic out of JSX

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — logic inside JSX
<button onClick={() => {
  if (balance < amount) return;
  dispatch({ type: 'STAKE', pool, amount });
}}>

// ✅ GOOD — handler extracted
function useBetPanel() {
  const handleStake = useCallback(() => {
    if (balance < amount) return;
    dispatch({ type: 'STAKE', pool, amount });
  }, [balance, amount, pool, dispatch]);

  return { handleStake };
}
```

## Move types out of component files

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — inline in component file
interface Props { pool: Pool; playerCount: number; }

// ✅ GOOD — in PoolCard.types.ts or imported from @repo/shared
import type { Pool } from '@repo/shared';
export interface PoolCardProps { pool: Pool; playerCount: number; }
```

## Prefer reusable presentational components

- UI components in `packages/ui/` — no business logic, no API calls
- Page-level components in `apps/web/` — compose UI components + data fetching
- Use TanStack Query for server state, never fetch in components directly
